docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS, Minn. "Our first priority must be to end the tragic struggle in Southeast Asia," the reedy, eternally passionate voice told the student audience, "and I therefore call for an immediate standstill cease-fire with international supervision, and new, free, internationally supervised elections."
